================================================================================
3. CONTRIBUTION RECORDING (기여 기록)
================================================================================

3.1 All modifications to the Software SHOULD be recorded using the PHAM Sign
    system to generate a Contribution Score.

3.2 The Contribution Score is calculated based on:
    - Byte changes (25%)
    - Text similarity changes (35%)
    - AST structure changes (30%)
    - Execution result changes (10%)

3.3 Contributors are encouraged, but not required, to sign their contributions.
    Unsigned contributions may not be eligible for revenue sharing.

================================================================================
4. REVENUE SHARING (수익 분배)
================================================================================

4.1 TRIGGER: Revenue sharing is activated when:
    - The Software or its derivatives generate more than $10,000 USD in 
      cumulative revenue, OR
    - A product using the Software is sold commercially

4.2 BASE ROYALTY: The Creator receives 6% of gross revenue.

4.3 CONTRIBUTOR ROYALTY: Remaining royalty pool is distributed proportionally
    based on Contribution Scores recorded in the Ledger.

4.4 CALCULATION:
    Creator Share = Revenue × 0.06
    
    For each Contributor:
    Share = (Contribution Score / Total Contribution Scores) × (Revenue × 0.04)

4.5 PAYMENT: Payments may be made via:
    - Cryptocurrency to the registered wallet addresses
    - Traditional bank transfer (if registered)
    - PHAM Token distribution

4.6 REPORTING: Revenue-generating users must report quarterly to:
    [opensource@qquarts.com]

================================================================================
5. BLOCKCHAIN VERIFICATION (블록체인 검증)
================================================================================

5.1 The original Software hash is recorded on the blockchain as proof of
    authorship and timestamp.

5.2 The Ledger of contributions is maintained on a public blockchain for
    transparency and immutability.

5.3 Anyone can verify:
    - Original authorship
    - Contribution history
    - Revenue distribution records

